# Apple code-signing + notarization configuration for `scripts/build-signed.sh`.
#
# Copy this to `.env.signing` (which is gitignored — NEVER commit the real one)
# and fill in your values. Nothing here is read unless you run the signed build.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1) SIGNING IDENTITY  (required)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# After installing your "Developer ID Application" certificate in Keychain,
# find the exact identity string with:
#     security find-identity -v -p codesigning
# Use the full name in quotes, including the team id in parentheses.
APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2) NOTARIZATION  (required) — choose ONE of the two methods below.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Method A: App Store Connect API key (recommended, no 2FA prompts) -------
# App Store Connect -> Users and Access -> Integrations -> App Store Connect API
#   APPLE_API_ISSUER   = the "Issuer ID" shown above the keys table
#   APPLE_API_KEY      = the "Key ID" from the table
#   APPLE_API_KEY_PATH = absolute path to the downloaded AuthKey_XXXX.p8 file
# APPLE_API_ISSUER="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
# APPLE_API_KEY="XXXXXXXXXX"
# APPLE_API_KEY_PATH="/Users/you/secrets/AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8"

# --- Method B: Apple ID + app-specific password (quick to set up) ------------
# Create an app-specific password at appleid.apple.com -> Sign-In & Security.
# Your Team ID is in the Apple Developer account membership page.
# APPLE_ID="you@example.com"
# APPLE_PASSWORD="abcd-efgh-ijkl-mnop"
# APPLE_TEAM_ID="TEAMID"
